Sentencas: Proton-conducting oxides offer a promising electrolyte solution for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) due to their high conductivity and low activation energy.
Titulo: Nanostructuring the electronic conducting La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ cathode for high-performance in proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells below 600°C

Sentencas: However, the lower operation temperature leads to a reduced cathode activity and thus a poorer fuel cell performance.
Titulo: Nanostructuring the electronic conducting La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ cathode for high-performance in proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells below 600°C

Sentencas: La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-delta (LSM) is the classical cathode material for high-temperature SOFCs, which lack features as a proper SOFC cathode material at intermediate temperatures.
Titulo: Nanostructuring the electronic conducting La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ cathode for high-performance in proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells below 600°C

Sentencas: Despite this, we here successfully couple nanostructured LSM cathode with proton-conducting electrolytes to operate below 600 degrees C with desirable SOFC performance.
Titulo: Nanostructuring the electronic conducting La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ cathode for high-performance in proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells below 600°C

Sentencas: Inkjet printing allows depositing nanostructured particles of LSM on Y-doped BaZrO3 (BZY) backbones as cathodes for proton-conducting SOFCs, which provides one of the highest power output for the BZY-based fuel cells below 600 degrees C.
Titulo: Nanostructuring the electronic conducting La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ cathode for high-performance in proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells below 600°C

Sentencas: This somehow changes the common knowledge that LSM can be applied as a SOFC cathode materials only at high temperatures (above 700 degrees C).
Titulo: Nanostructuring the electronic conducting La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ cathode for high-performance in proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells below 600°C
